{
  "stem": "9730.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I-- in that town, I think I also remember hearing about President Roosevelt's death, in our case, on April 13.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I believe he died on the 12th, but it was already the 13th when I heard it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as soon as the weather improved, though, we-- we knew we were ready for our advance.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we-- reports had reached us that a-- a town about five, six miles away from-- from there was ready to surrender.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were flying white flags.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So three jeeps were assigned to go in there and take the surrender.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One jeep was the military intelligence officer and his driver, who would take the actual civilian surrender.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The second one was a medical officer and his driver to see what we might find there that needed attention.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The third one was me, who had to go-- I had to search for any possible remnants of German troops in that town.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We-- so we set out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were really just six people that set out to-- to get to that town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And on the road, those four, five, six miles, I remember there-- there was still shelling going on from the other side of town.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were some German artillery units that-- that were shelling us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember driving along and looking down to the side of the jeep and seeing a shell drop right next to the jeep, and then rolling over into the ditch.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I hesitate to think what would have happened to me and this family had this shell not turned out to be a dud.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
